INSERT INTO quotes (id, content, author_id, views) VALUES (196701, 'My entire body shaking, I carefully unstrapped the seat belt and turned around as far as I could to look at the backseat.	Or rather, the dog that sat on it. He was panting, his eyes round, but there was nothing at all odd about him.	Other than the fact that I''d just heard him speak.	"You can''t talk," I told him.	"I think I can," he answered.', 6474, 0), (196702, 'How was I going to break it to my sister and brother that I was now a demon lord?', 6474, 0), (196703, 'It is the way of women to keep us humble, is it not?', 6474, 0), (196704, 'I''ll drive. But don''t you be turning into a dragon while you''re in the car. I don''t want those claws poking holes in my nice upholstery.', 6474, 0), (196705, 'Dragon form is generally reserved for mating and fighting. We found over the years that it was simply easier to blend in - physically speaking - if we resembled those around us. Do you wish to mate with me?', 6474, 0), (196706, 'For the record," I do not desire your body. Not that you''re hideous or anything, far from it. Even with those scars, your chest is really nice, and I like your legs because they aren''t scrawny, and you have nice shoulders and naughty bits, but I''ve never been one to put physical attributes ahead of more important things."	"Such as?" He had his hands on his hips when he asked the question, which just made me want to giggle again.	"Intelligence, a sense of humor, and oh yes, not being a mythical creature." I swallowed another giggle. "Not that it wasn''t a cool form, but still. I like my men without the sort of baggage that must go with being a shape-shifter."	"Is that so?" One eyebrow lifted.	"Yes."	"Then you will not like this." He pulled me against him, his mouth moving into place on mine, his breath hotter than I could have imagined. And then he kissed the very wits right out of my brain.', 6474, 0), (196707, 'Too much talking and not enough writhing in ecstasy. You will co